    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-01-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1469"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1469">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 855.48/143</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Germany</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_GJW1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gerard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the</hi>
                    <gloss type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State</hi>
                    </gloss>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Berlin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1915</hi>.</date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received 7.15 p. m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1305 [1355]. Department’s 999. <persName corresp="#p_VDH1">Van Dyke</persName>
                    informs me tax removed and money collected refunded. Have therefore asked German
                    Foreign Office to drop investigations previously requested at <persName
                        corresp="#p_VDH1">Van Dyke</persName>’s instance.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_GJW1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Gerard</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
